snippet.textDisplay:
When i saw a comment saying this was 8k i was like "nah man thats stupid!", my 1440p display(which is high end by most peoples standard) cant see that difference. Neither should there be a big difference from 4k monitors seeing 8k video. But i decided to test it out anyways!

And to my surprize i actually can see the difference. From 1080p to 1440p the diff is huge so much loss of detail especially when you are moving(im guessing YT downgrade). But even up to 4k i see more and more details on stills and better detail preservation when you were moving. And at 8k i got even more detail. Like the pores of your nose was like attacking me!
Im pretty sure i have good eyesight so i might be quite alone, but i felt like the jump from 1440p-4k was the same as 4k-8k. Just the starting point was so much better from 4k-8k but there was still a big difference in amount of detail.

snippet.textDisplay: I watched this video in 8K and .... yeah. My hardware is definitely not ready for it. I am watching on my workstation with 1080p monitor, huge difference in the sharpness between 8K and 1080p and very noticeable between 4K and 1080p as well, Ryzen 2700X and 1050Ti on Ubuntu 18.04.3 and I could hear the CPU fan ramp up, CPU usage hovering at 50-60% and my internet connection was doing 3-5Mb/s (30-40Mbit) so most people running 25Mbit internet can't even afford the bandwith. But I do like how amazingly crisp it looks and I would watch everything in 8K as long as I am not doing anything else in the background. Can't imagine 8K smart TVs have the "horsepower" to decode 8K YouTube though.
